   <category name='bungee'>

      <section name='form'>

         <para number='1' comment='Read form'>
         The form consists of a page full of legal jargon written in very small print. It starts out "The party of the first part..." and you discover that if you try to read any further, your eyes just drift and your mind wanders. At the bottom of the form is a space for your signature.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money to take jump'>
         You are about to sign the form when the droid grimaces, and says, "now now my dear, you can't get something for nothing, and Mr Shoddy doesn't like people who try to cheat him out of his earnings, so just you come back when you have got the 100 groats to pay for a jump, understand?" It pushes you back off the platform to the roof garden.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='insure'>

         <para number='1' comment='Platform - 528 - no insurance'>
         A small droid stops you from walking out onto the platform. "Oh no, sorry my dear," it says, "but you can't come onto the platform if you aren't insured, oh dear me no, it would be more than my job's worth to allow you." It pushes you back onto the roof garden.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='jump'>

         <para number='1' comment='Player takes the jump...'>
         Take a deep breath...
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         It then checks your weight and selects the appropriate length of bungee cord, attaches one end to your harness, the other to the edge of the platform, and pushes you off the edge...
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='2nd chunk'>
         ...you're falling...
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='3rd chunk'>
         ...plummeting down at high speed...
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='4th chunk'>
         ...but you realize you'll never get the full benefit of the experience unless you stop screaming and open your eyes. You see Earth's commercial district spread out below you, with the monorail line running towards the spaceport. As you watch, a shuttle takes off and zooms upwards, passing quite close to you as it heads out of sight into the planet's orbit.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='5th chunk'>
         Cars like little toys move along the roads, and the people on the sidewalks scurry back and forth like ants, but they are getting bigger as you fall.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='6th chunk'>
         You're getting very close to the ground now, and the vehicles look full sized as the ground looms up at you, and you think you are sure to hit it...
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='Successful landing'>
         Then the bungee cord reaches the end of its stretch and starts to contract again, and you bounce upwards again. Giving a yell of exuberance you travel back up the full height of the building until you reach the platform, where the droid operates some sort of catching device which scoops you up and pulls you back to safety.
         </para>

         <para number='9'>
         It unstraps you from the harness and pushes you back onto the roof garden, keen to get rid of you fast to make way for the next jumper.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='Announcement to 781'>
         Something above you catches your eye and you look up. Is it a bird? Is it a plane? Is it a desperate suicide leaping off the GA HQ to a certain death? No - it's a bungee jumper. As you watch, the cord reaches the end of its stretch and bounces %s back upwards, higher and higher, until you can't see the jumper any more.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='First death option'>
         Then the bungee cord reaches the end of its stretch, but before it can start to contract again, it snaps and you land head first on the sidewalk outside the Galactic Administration building, and suffer an excruciating pain before your brain gives out completely.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='Announce for 1st death'>
         Something above you catches your eye and you look up. Is it a bird? Is it a plane? Is it a desperate suicide leaping off the GA HQ to a certain death? No - it's a bungee jumper. As you watch, the cord reaches the end of its stretch but before it can contract and bounce the jumper up again, it snaps, allowing %s to hit the sidewalk with a sickening splat.
         </para>

         <para number='13'>
         Oh dear, that wasn't supposed to happen!
         </para>

         <para number='14'>
         An emergency team rushes in and within a remarkably short period of time, the late %s is scraped off the pavement and carted off to hospital.
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='2nd death option'>
         Then the bungee cord reaches the end of its stretch and starts to contract again, and you bounce upwards away from the ground, and giving a yell of exuberance you travel back up the full height of the building until you reach the platform. Now the droid is supposed to operate some sort of catching device to scoop you up and pull you back to safety, but something goes wrong and it gets tangled in the cord, which snaps and catapults you upwards.
         </para>

         <para number='16'>
         You are probably not moving quite fast enough to reach Earth orbit, but before you can find out, you collide with a shuttle taking off from the spaceport and are impaled on something spiky sticking out from its hull. You feel a momentary stab of terrible pain through your middle, and then you know no more.
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='Roomex - player takes a jump'>
         The small droid has just pushed %s off the edge! It's ok, though, it's a legitimate bungee jump with a harness.
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='Roomex - player returns safely'>
         The droid rushes forward and operates the catching mechanism. It pulls %s back to the safety of the platform and then ushers the successful jumper back to the roof garden.
         </para>

         <para number='19' comment='Roomex - player death 1'>
         The bungee cord suddenly goes slack - it has snapped, and the unfortunate %s has landed on the ground below you with a splat. The droid pulls the cord back up and replaces it with a new one, then shrugs and looks around to ask who is next.
         </para>

         <para number='20' comment='Roomex - player death 2'>
         The droid rushes forward and operates the catching mechanism, but something goes wrong and %s is catapulted high up into the sky. You here a clang as the unfortunate jumper collides with a passing shuttle, and dies a horrible death.
         </para>

