      <section name='godot'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Godot - 1105'>
         You point to a small blue cephalopod, swimming in a tank with many other alien sea creatures, and tell the waitdroid you want that one. He pulls it out using tongs and puts it onto a plate. The squid-like creature tries to crawl away but before it can escape you bite into it, releasing a flood of inky juice which glides down your throat like silk. There's a lot to be said for exotic alien foods!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Not enough groats'>
         You try to attract the attention of a waitdroid, but they can all see you can't afford to eat here, so they ignore you.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='lodge'>

         <para number='1' comment='Hunting lodge - eat food'>
         You examine the trays of food, picking out some morsels that look particularly tasty, and put together a plate that makes up a substantial meal. As you eat it, you can tell that no expense has been spared on the catering.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Hunting lodge - drink'>
         You make your selection from the many bottles on offer, and pour yourself a drink. You have no idea what it is, but it's brightly colored - in fact it seems to change color as you hold the glass up to the light - and it fizzes on your tongue. Very refreshing!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='lucky7'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Lucky 7 - 1479'>
         You whistle for some food, and a waitdroid brings you Elvis' favorite snack: a grilled peanut butter sandwich, stuffed with bananas, bacon and honey. You don't want to appear to be a wimp, so you eat this rather peculiar combination, and discover it's not as bad as it looks. Long live the King!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Not enough groats'>
