      <section name='acorn'>

         <para number='1' comment='Examine/ex acorn charm'>
         The acorn charm is life-sized and is made out of silver. The seed part of the charm is smooth to the touch, and by contrast the cupule is rough and dimpled. It is a perfect replica of the real thing. Squeeze it to make it grow.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Squeeze acorn charm'>
         You give the acorn a squeeze, and that makes the outer covering split into two halves, revealing the seed inside - also made from silver. The seed starts to quiver and shake, and then it too splits as a small shoot emerges and seeks the light.
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
         The shoot grows and sprouts silver leaves, then grows some more and produces branches and more leaves, until you are holding a perfect miniature oaktree. You can hear a rustling sound as the leaves are caressed by a breeze, and there's a hint of birdsong and the smell of spring.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         Then the silver leaves start to shrivel, drying up and falling off. They hit the ground and vanish, the branches are pulled back into the trunk of the tiny tree, which shrinks and returns to its seed. Finally the acorn closes up and the two halves seal up into a perfect whole again.
         </para>

