         Puckleberry stands up and gives a little bob of the head. "Greetings," he says. "I assume you are here about the mission...?"
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Nomatch'>
         Mr Puckleberry just shakes his head and says, in an exasperated tone of voice, "I haven't got time to talk about that now, I am in the middle of dealing with a serious crisis, as you should know."
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Yes - topic is mission'>
         You introduce yourself to Mr Puckleberry and tell him that yes, you are here about the mission.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Yes - no topic'>
         Mr Puckleberry looks puzzled. "Yes what?" he asks.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='No - topic is mission'>
         Mr Puckleberry looks a little taken aback by your response, but he recovers his poise, and says, "In that case, I won't take up any more of your time," and goes back to his paperwork.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='No - topic is somebody'>
         Mr Puckleberry looks disappointed. "Oh well," he says, "If you won't help us, we will have to look elsewhere for assistance," and he goes back to his paperwork.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='No - no topic'>
         Mr Puckleberry looks puzzled. "No what?" he asks.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='Mission - already briefed'>
         "Well, as I have already told you..." Mr Puckleberry does not look pleased at having to repeat himself but he realizes it is necessary.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='Mission information'>
         He clears his throat and seems a little reluctant to speak at first. "It's a bit of an awkward situation," he finally says. "The Guild finds it a trifle embarrassing, but we need the help of somebody outside the Guild - by which I mean, someone other than one of our officials."
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='Info continues for members'>
         "As a member of the Guild you may know a little about how we operate.
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='And for non-members'>
         "You're not yet a Guild member so you won't know anything about how we operate.
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='Then continues for everyone'>
         "As it happens, by great coincidence, a muck-raking reporter called Godarkly has recently published some information about our practices in that pestilential rag, the Fed2 Star. Much as it pains me to admit it, the facts are substantially correct, so you should read the article for some background knowledge.
         </para>

         <para number='16'>
         I suggest you call it up now and take a look - you can read it at http://www.ibgames.net/fednews/2006/061022/official05.html - then tell me when you are ready for me to carry on."
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='Ready/carry on/continue'>
         "Good. Then I will continue," says the accountant. "We have a problem with an applicant - an asteroid called Graveyard (my goodness, the names these POs choose!) There are some... how shall I put it... irregularities. Yes, indeed, considerable irregularities." He nods at you in a significant manner, as if he expects you to understand what those irregularities might be.
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='Irregularities'>
         You ask him to expand on these irregularities, and he continues the briefing. "The owner is proposing to sell commodities at prices far, far lower than any other agricultural planet, and we can't see how he can do that. It makes no sense, and we are worried that it is in fact a front for something more sinister - money laundering, perhaps, or some other criminal activity.
         </para>

         <para number='19'>
         "If that is the case then we need to know so we can inform the Galactic Administration - we would never, of course, allow such a planet into the trading network.
         </para>

         <para number='20'>
         "If, on the other hand, the PO has genuinely come up with a way to produce goods at rock-bottom prices... well, that would be an equally serious matter, with implications for the entire galactic economy.  This needs to be investigated..." he gives another of those significant nods.
         </para>

         <para number='21' comment='Investigat'>
         Puckleberry frowns. "We did of course despatch one of our accountants to take a look at the planet, but it is most distressing... most distressing... he vanished, disappeared without a trace. We sent a second accountant and instructed him to take all possible precautions, and we know he has landed on the planet, but he has communicated with us to the effect that he is afraid to proceed any further."
         </para>

         <para number='22'>
         Puckleberry sighs. "I suppose he can't be blamed, he is an accountant not a daredevil. So he needs help from somebody more suited to the task.
         </para>

         <para number='23'>
         "We are hoping that you, %s, are that somebody. Somebody not immediately identifiable with the Guild; somebody more used to the dangers found in the darker corners of the Galaxy; somebody, in short, who can find out what is happening and report back to our accountant.
         </para>

         <para number='24'>
         "Are you that somebody?"
         </para>

         <para number='25' comment='Somebody'>
         Mr Puckleberry's mouth twitches in the closest he ever gets to a smile. "Excellent," he said. "Now, Graveyard (charming name!) is not yet on the navy's official spacelanes so you have to navigate there manually. I have the directions here..." he reads from some of the papers he is clutching.
         </para>

         <para number='26'>
         "Enter the asteroid belt as normal, and then head east for two sectors and you will find the asteroid. Board your shuttle as normal to land. Then make sure you talk to our operative before you do anything; he'll give you what information he has.
         </para>

         <para number='27'>
         "That's all I can tell you, so off you go."
         </para>

         <para number='28' comment='Reward for Commanders'>
         "Allow me to bestow a reward upon you, just a small token of the Guild's esteem and gratitude.  I have added the sum of 20,000 groats to your bank balance to help towards paying off your loan."
