         Victor looks embarrassed and confesses that he doesn't know anything about that subject.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='bye'>
         "Oh! Ummm, goodbye. It was nice talking to you." Victor looks round in a slightly bemused fashion.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='job/work'>
         "I run the test for people who want to join the Magellan Society," Victor explains. "This is the first time I've done it on my own," he smiles diffidently.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='earth'>
         "It's very busy and crowded everywhere on Earth, and people are so brash," Victor confides. "Sometimes I find it a bit overwhelming. I was brought up in Selena - that's the main city on the Moon - which is much slower." He smiles nervously, obviously worried that you might take offense.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='selena/moon'>
         Victor smiles. "That's where I come from. I never thought I'd go anywhere else, like Earth. But then I won a Magellan scholarship to study here." He looks a little homesick.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='exhibition/where'>
         "This is a semi-permanent exhibition mounted by the Magellan Society to show the sort of work the society does. We picked some of the more exciting moments!" He waves an arm in the direction of the exhibits and nearly knocks over a vase of flowers.
         </para>

