      <section name='boss'>

         <para number='1' comment='hello'>
         The boss greets you effusively. "Welcome, welcome, and how may we be of assistance to you? We issue the various permits relating to buildings." He rubs his hands together as he speaks.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='bye'>
         The boss rubs his hands together and tells you, "I'm sure that we will do business in the future."
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='job/work'>
         "I'm the head of the Zoning and Planning department of the Galactic Administration. We are the ones who issue the permits that allow the different types of building activities." He gives you an oily smirk.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='gaelaan (1)'>
         The boss's good humour vanishes. "Those scum," he hisses. "If I had my way..." Realising who he is speaking to he stops ranting with an effort and continues in a more reasonable tone. "The Cult of Gaelaan opposes everything that the Galactic Administration stands for - hard work, respect for authority, orderliness and adherence to regulations."
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='gaelaan (2)'>
         "The Cult of Gaelaan seeks to subvert all these virtues and encourages workers to be lazy and expect help from our sworn enemies, the Martians." He refuses to discuss the cult any further.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Galactic Admin'>
         He nods sagely and intones portentously, "We in the Galactic Administration exist only to serve the interests of the human race." He bestows on you what is obviously supposed to be a benevolent smile. Unfortunately, it comes out as more like an insincere smirk.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='zoning'>
         "Zoning is the process of laying down where different types of buildings can be built. Of course these days most building is underground, to conserve the surface area for agriculture. Indeed, this city is the only major set of above-ground buildings left on the planet."
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='planning'>
         "Planning encompasses ensuring that an area being developed has all the necessary amenities - both physical like water and power and access facilities, and social like schools and shops. You'd be surprised how often people forget that these things are just as necessary as the dwellings and commercial buildings!"
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='bribe/backhander'>
         The boss looks shocked. "B-b-bribes?" he stutters. "I can assure you that no one in this office even knows the meaning of the word!" He glances at you slyly. "But you do have to prove that you are worthy..."
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='worthy (1)'>
         "Worthy... Yes..." He nods sagely. "You do need to be worthy to be the owner of a Galactic Administration permit. For instance, a donation to charity would indicate a large degree of worthiness." He endeavours to look modest, and fails miserably. "As it happens, I am an authorised collector for the Orion Sector Fund for the Care of Distressed Bureaucrats, which I'm sure you will agree is a very worthy cause."
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='worthy (2)'>
         "Were you to include a slithy tove or two (depending on the exact permit you wanted) with your purchase of the permit, then I'm sure there would be no obstacles." He tries to look nonchalant.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='permit (1)'>
         "Ah yes - permits. This office handles a number of different permits, and you need to meet different conditions to apply for each of them. However, in all cases you need to satisfy me that you are a person worthy of being granted a permit." He smirks, and you can almost see the greed shining in his eyes.
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='permit (2)'>
         "We are currently issuing warehouse permits, depot permits, storage permits, and factory permits. Discussions are underway on the possibility of issuing other types of permit, but they have not yet come to fruition."
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='warehouse'>
         "Warehouse permits allow you to buy a warehouse when you are a merchant. This is very useful, because you can store cargo without the risk of having it end up in Heisenberg's warehouse. You need to be a merchant with 300 successful trades under your belt, and at least 700,000ig in the bank. The permit costs 600,000ig, and, of course, you must prove you're worthy of having a permit."
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='depot (1)'>
         "Ah yes. Depot permits are issued to manufacturers to allow them to build their depots higher than two stories. The ban on high buildings goes back to Ming, who didn't want anything to be higher than his statue. Unfortunately, the Galactic Administration has no procedures for repealing ordinances, but we can mitigate the effects by issuing depot permits."
         </para>

         <para number='16' comment='depot (2)'>
         "To buy a depot permit you need to be at least an industrialist, and your company will need to put down the sum of 1,000,000ig. There is no limit on the number of depots you can upgrade once you have the permit." Almost as an afterthought he adds, "Oh! And you will need to convince me of your worthiness to be a permit holder."
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='storage'>
         "The Galactic Administration frowns on the use of temporary storage for finished goods at factories, because of the security implications. However, it will issue storage permits that allow you to upgrade the storage in your factories to 450 tons. Obviously you need to be a manufacturer and it costs 500,000ig. I'm sure you can prove your worthiness to hold such a permit."
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='factory (1)'>
         The boss shakes his head. "Very difficult. The permit enables you to apply efficiency increases to the factory. This means that you employ less workers, and the unions don't like that. They monitor the issue of these permits to ensure that they are issued only to the most worthy."
         </para>

         <para number='19' comment='factory (2)'>
         "To get one of these permits you have to be a manufacturer and the cost to your company is 5,000,000ig. You do need to be a very worthy citizen, though." A passing clerk whispers, "That means his mate in Union Central wants a cut. You need to be prepared to pay an extra two slithy toves when you buy this permit."
         </para>

         <para number='20' comment='additional for permits'>
