         <para number='5' comment='already done a stat today'>
         At the end of her thorough examination, she frowns at you. "No, I can't risk it," she says. "You've had one of your personal attributes tampered with today already, and there's a limit to what a body can take. If anything should go wrong, the legal ramifications just don't bear thinking about." She shudders. "Come back tomorrow and we can do it then. I'll be here. I'm always here."
         </para>

         <para number='6'>
         She pushes you back into the center of the room and returns to her work.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Dex is already maxed'>
         At the end of her thorough examination, she turns to you with a look of regret. "Sorry, it can't be done," she says. "Your dexterity can't possibly be boosted any higher than it is now. Shame, because I would love to take your slithy, but it wouldn't work and might possibly kill you, which would really complicate things." She returns to her work with a forlorn shrug.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='Increase dex'>
         Once she has finished her thorough examination, she turns to you with a look of approval. "Right, let's do it," she says. "Give me the slithy first." You hand over the certificate and she tucks it inside her white lab coat. "Now," she continues, "hold still, this won't hurt... much..."
         </para>

         <para number='9'>
         She presses a button and your body is bathed in a cold, blue light. Every part of you tingles, and then itches, and you want to writhe around and scratch yourself raw but you can't move, and you're sure you cannot endure another moment of this without going mad, and you try to scream but your throat is paralyzed, and then...
         </para>

         <para number='10'>
         It stops. Blessed relief. In fact, more than relief, you feel a lot better than you did before the treatment, aware of every part of your body and able to control everything much better.
         </para>

         <para number='11'>
         The scientist gives you a quick once-over and looks satisfied. "Works every time," she says. "At least, it does now we've got the bugs out." She pats you on the back and turns back to her work.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='coda if now maxed'>
