         <para number='2' comment='They are signed up'>
         Simon takes your comm unit and attaches a small electronic gadget to it. You look startled, so Simon explains.
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
         "Don't worry, I'm not breaking it. Ming was a sneaky so-and-so," he says. "He set things up so the animals would avoid anyone whose comm unit gave out a certain signal. That meant he could choose who was safe, and who was in danger." He gives a little shiver as he thinks about the maliciousness of Ming. "This gadget on your comm unit will constantly transmit that signal, so the beasts will leave you alone now."
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         He loses his smile for a moment, as he hands your comm unit back to you. "One word of warning - the gadget is pretty delicate. If your comm unit gets knocked about or damaged, you could lose the protection. If that happens, best thing is get out fast and come back here, otherwise who knows what might happen."
         </para>

         <para number='5'>
         Simon explains, "One final thing before you can go. It's just a formality, a legal thing, but I need you to confirm for the record that you accept the risks and won't hold WWT responsible for anything that happens to you." To comply with Simon's request, type "I confirm".
         </para>

