         <para number='8' comment='elves'>
         "My elves are very versatile, Santa says. "Their traditional job is to make toys in the workshop but I have trained some of them to diversify so I now have housework elves, laundry elves, cooking elves, and of course the security elves."
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='housework elves'>
         "The housework elves come in several different sizes," Santa explains. "Big ones with long arms can reach up high to dust the top shelves and get cobwebs off the ceiling. Little ones can clean under the furniture and in all the nooks and crannies. They are very efficient."
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='laundry elves'>
         Santa explains, "They do a very good job; they make sure I always have a clean robe to put on, and they are careful not to mix up the red robes with my white underthings. Funny, though, even they can't stop the occasional sock from going missing..."
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='cooking elves'>
         Santa smiles, and says, "Mrs Claus used to do all my cooking but I have to be honest, the elves do a much better job of it. She doesn't mind, she's got plenty of real work to keep her occupied."
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='security elves'>
         Santa frowns and tells you, "I don't like the fact that I have to have them, but after that ghastly business a few years ago, I just can't be too careful."
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='ghastly business'>
         "I think it was hushed up so you may not have heard about it," Santa explains. "I set off on my deliveries, and the Imperial Navy shot down my sleigh! I crashed in the middle of the wilderness." Santa shudders at the memory.
         </para>

         <para number='14'>
         "Luckily I wasn't hurt. I didn't think I'd be able to complete my deliveries; Christmas morning dawned and there were no presents in stockings. Children were rioting, so the Galactic Administration stepped in and found someone to sort things out. I don't know the name of the helpful person who rescued me, but if it hadn't been for them, I'd probably still be stranded up that blasted tree even now.
         </para>

         <para number='15'>
         "The navy were very apologetic of course. It turned out that it wasn't their fault - someone had sabotaged the transponder on my sleigh, so their friend/foe identification whatsit thought I was an alien invader or something. We never did find out who was responsible. So this year, taking no chances, some of the workers have morphed into security elves. They'll keep me safe."
         </para>

         <para number='16' comment='mrs claus/wife/list'>
         "Mrs Claus is in charge of the naughty/nice lists now. It's all computerized, you know. I don't understand how it works at all, but she just pushes a button and out come the lists, in just the right order for me. It's marvelous!"
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='grotto'>
         Santa beams with pride. "I hope you like my grotto. I designed it myself, and the elves built it for me. It can get a bit cold, all this ice, but it's very beautiful, so I can put up with it for the short time it'll be here. Besides, my robes are nice and warm."
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='big night/deliver'>
         "Of course, the night before Christmas is the culmination of my whole year's work. That's what it is all about. Thanks to the magic fairy dust that powers my sleigh, and the special powers of the reindeer, I am able to visit every child in the whole Galaxy and leave the presents that they will find when they wake up on Christmas day.
         </para>

         <para number='19'>
         "This year is the first for a long time that I have had to deliver outside the Solar System - last year, the link had only just reopened so I didn't have to.
         </para>

         <para number='20'>
         "It has increased my workload considerably - I love my work, but it's very tiring. In subjective time, I have to stay awake making the deliveries for weeks, even though it all takes place in one night of real time. And all I have to sustain me is the milk and cookies the children leave out for me."
         </para>

         <para number='21' comment='Reindeer/dasher'>
         "The reindeer are magic, of course - how else could they fly?" explains Santa. "Rudolph is the leader of the pack, or herd, or whatever the collective noun for a group of magical deer is. He came to me after the others, but they all accept him. The others are Dasher, Dancer, Prancer, Vixen, Comet, Cupid, Blitzen and... oh, what's the other one, I can never remember?"
         </para>

         <para number='22' comment='donner'>
         "That's it!" Santa exclaims. "Donner. That's the name I always forget."
         </para>

         <para number='23' comment='rudolph'>
         "He's the leader because of his red nose - it helps to light the way," explains Santa. "It took a while for the other reindeer to accept him, but they saw how talented he was eventually."
         </para>

         <para number='24' comment='olive'>
         Santa looks cross. "No, there isn't a reindeer called Olive. That's a stupid joke. I get fed up with being asked about it, and so do the reindeer, let me tell you."
         </para>

         <para number='25' comment='milk'>
         Santa leans forward and whispers to you, "Well, between you and me, I prefer a pint of Diesel's Old Peculiar, but all they ever leave me is milk, or sometimes a small glass of sherry." He sighs.
         </para>

         <para number='26' comment='cookies'>
         "Now I do like cookies," says Santa. "Chocolate chip are my favorite, although I am also partial to oatmeal, honey and raisin cookies." He smacks his lips at the thought. "Sometimes I get left the most peculiar flavors, though - one child left me some candied zlitherworm chip cookies last year. They were disgusting. Even the reindeer wouldn't touch them."
         </para>

         <para number='27' comment='bye'>
         "Bye bye, my child," says Santa. You clamber off his lap and he wishes you a very merry Christmas.
         </para>

         <para number='28' comment='nomatch'>
