      <section name='sleigh'>

         <para number='1' comment='Sleighride - get into sleigh'>
         You climb into the sleigh and seat yourself on the seat where Santa's bottom normally sits...
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Sleighride'>
         An elf drapes a thick fur rug over you, and you snuggle into it. He steps back, and the reindeer start to move. The runners of the sleigh slide easily over the packed snow, and it soon picks up speed, sliding along with a swooshing sound. The wind rushes past you, and you're glad of the fur rug!
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Sleighride - message 1'>
         Santa's grotto vanishes out of sight behind you, as the sleigh zooms along. There's nothing to be seen except a vast expanse of white. Then the noise of the runners changes, and you realize the reindeer are running along the length of a huge glacier. They pound along, their hooves ringing on the ice, and then you can suddenly see that the ice falls away as the glacier ends in a sheer cliff.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         But the reindeer don't stop, they speed up, and you start to scream as the sleigh plummets off the end... and then flies into the air.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Sleighride - message 2'>
         Of course, you should have remembered that Santa's sleigh can fly! The reindeers' legs keep on galloping even though they are flying; perhaps that's how they propel themselves through the air. You look down and see that you are now flying over Earth's wilderness area; you can see the patchwork of different greens, the brown of the swampy area, the blue and white of the various rivers.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Sleighride - message 3'>
         The reindeers turn to the left, and the sleigh tilts over alarmingly as it banks into the turn. You wish it had been fitted with seatbelts! Far below you are the lights of Earth's spaceport; as you watch, you can see a shuttle launching itself from the landing pad to dock with one of the ships waiting in orbit.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Sleighride - message 4'>
         The reindeers seem to gather themselves, then leap upwards; the sleigh follows the launching shuttle and leaves the planet behind. Somehow, there's a bubble of air surrounding you even though the sleigh seems open to the vacuum of space. Below you is the familiar "blue marble" that is the Earth seen from space, which you have seen so many times on your ship's view screen, but seeing it directly is a very different thing.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='Sleighride - message 5'>
         Leaving Earth behind, the reindeer set course for the further reaches of the Solar System. You zoom past Mars and its two tiny moons, take a turn around the giant Jupiter, then approach Saturn where you can take in the view of the magnificent rings.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='Sleighride - message 6'>
         The reindeer turn again, and head back towards the sun. A little blue dot starts to get bigger, and bigger, until it fills your view and the sleigh is once again in orbit around the Earth. The deer do a couple of circuits around the planet, taking a lower orbit each time, and then zoom downwards at frightening speed, heading towards the snowy wastes of the north pole.
         </para>

         <para number='10'>
         The sleigh gets closer and closer to the ground, plummeting at great speed, until you are sure it's going to crash... but suddenly, it touches down, the reindeers' hooves make contact with the snow, and the sleigh slithers to a halt outside Santa's grotto again.
         </para>

         <para number='11'>
         An elf helps you out of the sleigh and chucks the fur robe back onto the seat, ready for the next passenger.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='Examine sleigh'>
         This is the real sleigh Santa uses to delivery presents on Christmas day. The reindeer are not the famous ones whose names you know; those only do the job on the day, and for now these younger deer are being allowed to pull the sleigh as a training exercise. You peek into the sleigh, and can see an empty turkish delight box under one of the seats.
         </para>

         <para number='13'>
         To take a sleigh ride, "enter sleigh".
         </para>

